{
  "stem": "9168.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then we also had seated next to us, a German monitor for the American court reporters who had been-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] one could never have been a member of the Nazi party to be on the Allied payroll.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we had a wonderful monitor who was a German national, seated next to us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And next to him were the German court reporters.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we did not have-- the order was, no fraternization.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So we did not mix at all with any of the-- the indigenous population.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Our boss was General Telford Taylor, who was one of the major prosecutors on Goering's trial, under Robert Jackson.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was the Chief Prosecutor for the 12 subsequent trials, of which the Nazi Doctors' Trial was the first.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were Drexel Sprecher, S-P-R-E-C-H-E-R.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We was from, I think, Washington DC.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also American, oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was not military.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "General Taylor was the military person.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were other military officers who were involved in the pre-trial interrogations.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Colonel Amen, I remember, for one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had-- there was a prosecutor-- let me see-- Benjamin Ferencz, F-E-R-E-N-C-Z.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't remember that he was assigned specifically to the Doctors' Trial.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "These attorneys were not someone that I really knew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "McHaney was another prosecutor.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But there were many, many.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not in the 12 subsequent trials, other than, at the end of Goering's trial, which was an international trial with the four countries, the judges.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Four judges, one from each of the victorious powers, the United States, France, Great Britain-- representing Great Britain and Northern Ireland-- and the Soviet Russia.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Four judges and four alternate judges, so there were actually eight judges on the bench in Goering's trial.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
